column18:
Dear participant,

You will be taking part in the project designed for the course “The Data Science of Everyday Music Listening” under the supervision of the University of Amsterdam.

Purpose of the research project
The purpose of the project is to study whether and how parents’ musical preferences are reflected in the music their children like to
listen to.

Who can take part?
This study is open to university students aged 18 years or older, and one of their parents or primary caregivers with whom they lived for a significant part of their childhood.


Instructions
Please carefully read the instructions provided at the beginning of the survey before responding to the questions. If you are a student participant, you are asked to share this survey link with one of your parents or primary caregivers with whom you lived for a significant part of your childhood. Both you and your parent/caregiver should complete the survey, using the same family code, so that your responses can be linked anonymously for analysis.

Voluntary participation & risks
You will be participating in this research on a voluntary basis. This means you are free to stop
taking part at any stage without consequences or penalty. If you decide to stop or withdraw
your consent, all the information gathered up until then will be permanently deleted. This
research has no known risks.

Privacy

The information gathered will be used for publication in scientific journals only. Fully
anonymized data may be available online in tandem with these scientific publications. We
guarantee that you will remain anonymous under all circumstances. Your personal
information will not be viewed by third parties without your express permission. Participants
can request more information from the researcher at any time about their rights as data
subjects under the EU privacy law, the GDPR.

Further Information
For further information, please contact Grace Nguyen (khanh.minh.nguyen@student.uva.nl) or dr. Ashley Burgoyne (j.a.burgoyne@uva.nl). If you have any complaints regarding this project, you can contact
the Secretary of the Ethics Committee of the Faculty of Humanities of the University of
Amsterdam (commissie-ethiek-fgw@uva.nl).

Informed consent
I have been clearly informed about the research project and I consent to participate in this
research. I retain the right to revoke this consent without having to provide any reasons for my
decision. I am aware that I am entitled to discontinue the research at any time and can
withdraw my participation.
